{
    "id": "camerautil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "CameraUtil",
    "description": "Turn an object into the game's camera, read where the active camera is, and control how smoothly the view blends when switching cameras.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/camerautil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "camerautil",
        "camera",
        "view",
        "blend"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "PhysicsUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/physicsutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "LightUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/lightutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "CameraUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The **camera** is the player's eye into your world — it decides what they see. `CameraUtil` turns an object into a camera, tells you where the active camera is, and controls how smoothly the view glides when you switch between cameras."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Making a camera"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`AddCamera` turns the object into the active camera. After this, what the object \"sees\" is what the player sees."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class GameCamera",
                "{",
                "    void OnInit()",
                "    {",
                "        CameraUtil.AddCamera(this);",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Moving the camera"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "You move and aim a camera the same way you move any object — with [UniObjectUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil). A common pattern is to follow the player every frame in `OnUpdate`:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "void OnUpdate()",
                "{",
                "    // Sit a few units behind and above the player.",
                "    vector3 playerPos = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(player);",
                "    vector3 camPos = playerPos + VectorUtil.New(0.0, 4.0, -7.0);",
                "    UniObjectUtil.SetPosition(this, camPos);",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "warning",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "To move a camera, use `UniObjectUtil.SetPosition` — **not** `SetWorldPosition`, which silently does nothing on a camera. To aim it, use `SetRotation` with `QuaternionUtil.LookRotation` (see [UniObjectUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil#block-013))."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Reading the active camera"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "These tell you about whichever camera is currently showing — useful for spawning things in front of the player or checking the viewing angle."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it returns"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`GetActiveCamera()`", "The current camera object."],
                ["`GetActiveCameraPosition()`", "Where the current camera is (a `vector3`)."],
                ["`GetActiveCameraRotation()`", "Which way the current camera faces (a `quaternion`)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Smoothing camera switches"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "When you switch from one camera to another, the view can either cut instantly or glide across. `SetCameraBlendTime` sets how many seconds that glide takes."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Take 1.5 seconds to ease between cameras.",
                "CameraUtil.SetCameraBlendTime(1.5);",
                "",
                "// Use 0 for an instant cut.",
                "CameraUtil.SetCameraBlendTime(0.0);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`AddCamera`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetActiveCamera`", "—"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetActiveCameraPosition`", "—"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`GetActiveCameraRotation`", "—"],
                ["`void`", "`SetCameraBlendTime`", "`float seconds`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "For a camera that follows the player smoothly, write your follow logic in `OnUpdate` (or `OnPostUpdate` so it runs after the player has moved) and blend toward the target spot with `VectorUtil.SmoothLerp`."
        }
    ]
}
